## Becoming a Maintainer

Sustained, high-quality contributions plus demonstrated good judgment. Nominated by
an existing maintainer and approved by maintainer consensus (see §5).

## 4. Contribution Process

```
Open an issue describing the bug/feature (for non-trivial changes).
Fork and create a feature branch.
```
### 1. Placeholder



```
Follow CONTRIBUTING.md (../CONTRIBUTING.md): keep the core dependency-light,
preserve verify_chain() integrity, follow PEP 8, and never commit sensitive
data (data/, private keys).
Add or update tests; ensure the full test suite passes.
Open a pull request. At least one maintainer approval is required to merge;
security-sensitive or consensus-critical changes require two.
Maintainers may request changes or decline contributions that conflict with the
mission, license, or policies.
```
## 5. Decision-Making

```
Lazy consensus for routine changes: if no maintainer objects within a
reasonable review window, the change proceeds.
Consensus-seeking for significant changes (architecture, cryptography,
governance, license-adjacent matters): discussed openly; maintainers aim for
agreement. If consensus cannot be reached, a simple majority of active
maintainers decides; ties are resolved by the lead maintainer.
All decisions must respect the Code of Conduct (CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) and project
policies.
```
## 6. Releases

```
Versioning follows Semantic Versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH). Current line:
2.x.
Release checklist: tests green, docs updated, changelog written, security review
for crypto/auth/consensus changes.
Security fixes are prioritized and may trigger out-of-band patch releases (see
SECURITY.md (SECURITY.md)).
```
## 7. Security Governance

Vulnerability reports are handled privately by the security team per the
Security Policy (SECURITY.md), including coordinated disclosure and advisories.

## 8. Changes to Governance and Policies

Changes to this document or any policy in this directory require a pull request and
maintainer consensus. Material changes are recorded in release notes and the policy
version headers are updated.

## 9. Code of Conduct

All participants must follow the Code of Conduct (CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). Enforcement
is the responsibility of maintainers and community moderators.

